<TITLE> Ministers, MPs misused police: IGP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khulna, June 1 (bdnews24.com) -- Inspector general of police Noor Mohammad said Friday that the police had been used by ministers and MPs for their past misdeeds. "That's why people lost confidence in the police," the country's police chief said in his address to the inauguration of a model police station in Sonadanga of Khulna metropolitan area. Citing the example of a former state minister allegedly taking Tk 20 crore in bribe for a murder cover-up, as reported by some newspapers, the IGP said that if any corruption, nepotism or harassment charge brought against any police officer was proven, he would be sacked. "The situation has now changed. It is now time for the common man to speak," the IGP said. Khulna Metropolitan Police commissioner Nazmul Haq presided over the inauguration. bd
